=============================================================================
Application Runtime 2.0 ART
=============================================================================

Successor to Dalvik introduced in Android 4.4
Take .java to .class to .dex to .oat
Garbage Collections enhacements
OAT File (.dex)
 3x bigger than original dex file. Because the Dalvik bytecode and the native
 instruction set. Also it has OAT Data which links the Dalvik code to the
 native instruction set
OAT Ahead Of Time
 If it is an application you download, during install time, we compile to OAT
 format. If it is a pre loaded /(system/app) it is already precompiled into
 OAT format
